_header: Death bringeth down low that been bold
Subjects: death; transitoriness, of life; youth; sermons, verse in
_description: The inevitability of death, in a Latin sermon — two couplets in a Latin sermon

BodLatTheD1.Transcription:
Deth bringith down lowe þat ben beldeDeth takyth ȝong as
                    well as helde þe more stowt þou art & more gayparauentur
                    þe ner þi endyng day
